# Hosts that block CI runners with 999 / 403 / 429 responses (bot protection),
# not because the links are dead. Curated from the hosts actually present in
# this site's content so that a RED link check means a genuinely broken link.
# These platforms gate non-browser clients regardless of whether the target
# exists, so checking them from CI is always a false positive. Trim any you'd
# rather have actively verified. See docs/followups.md for the full backstory.

# Own domains: checked locally via dist/ (internal links) and by deploy.yml's
# smoke-test job (liveness). Hostinger 403s the CI runner IP, so checking the
# fully-qualified self-links here is always a false positive.
mindiweik\.com
wip-podcast\.com

# Social platforms (return 999 / login-wall to non-browser clients)
linkedin\.com
tiktok\.com
instagram\.com

# Video (bot-throttled / 429)
youtube\.com
youtube-nocookie\.com
youtu\.be

# Course / media / design / docs platforms (403 to CI runners)
canva\.com
substack\.com
udemy\.com
medium\.com
loom\.com
oreilly\.com
goodreads\.com
meetup\.com
npmjs\.com
raspberrypi\.com
openai\.com
claude\.ai
gitlab\.com
inc\.com
techopedia\.com

# Intentional 404: this blog post demonstrates a deliberately mistyped URL
# ("imaaaages" instead of "images") to show a failed request.
https://api\.thecatapi\.com/v1/imaaaages/search
